    "source_sections": {
      "references": "[SaZy54] Salem, R. and Zygmund, A., Some properties of trigonometric series whose terms have\nrandom signs. Acta Math. (1954), 245-301.",
      "remarks": "A problem of Salem and Zygmund \\cite{SaZy54}. Chung showed that, for almost all $t$, there exist infinitely many $n$ such that\\[M_n(t) \\ll \\left(\\frac{n}{\\log\\log n}\\right)^{1/2}.\\]Erd\\H{o}s (unpublished) showed that for almost all $t$ and every $\\epsilon>0$ we have $\\lim_{n\\to \\infty}M_n(t)/n^{1/2-\\epsilon}=\\infty$."
    },
